===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈkaʊn.tənt/}}

===Etymology 1===
* First attested in the mid 15th century.
* {{suffix|account|ant}}
* From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|acuntant|lang=frm}}.
* Compare {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|accomptant|lang=fr}}.
* See also ''[[account]]''.

====Noun====
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# One who [[render]]s [[account]]; one [[accountable]].
# A [[reckoner]], or someone who maintains [[financial]] matters for a person(s)
# {{context|accounting}} One who is skilled in, keeps, or adjusts, accounts; an officer in a public office, who has charge of the accounts.
# {{context|accounting}} One whose profession includes organizing, maintaining and [[audit]]ing the records of another. The records are usually, but not always, financial records.

